<div id="review_3822983060" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3822983060" />
    <a title="Jessy Hrdlicka" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/110372903-jessy-hrdlicka"><img alt="Jessy Hrdlicka" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1592654620p2/110372903.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3822983060?book_show_action=true">Feb 15, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jessy Hrdlicka" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jessy Hrdlicka" href="/user/show/110372903-jessy-hrdlicka">Jessy Hrdlicka</a>
      </span>

          marked it as to-read




        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3822983060" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3747618917259174555">I thought this was an Odd Thomas book, and when I read the Odd Thomas books, I felt as if he had plagarized himself...I didn&apos;t really get into the main character, found the situation to be too unrealistic to be relatable. But don&apos;t take my word for it, the Odd Thomas series has never been my favorites, I read them once and then never again. I am a great fan of his stand alone books, of which there are over 60. I collect them and I am currently doing a Koontz re-read of all his titles that have c</span>
  <span id="freeText3747618917259174555" style="display:none">I thought this was an Odd Thomas book, and when I read the Odd Thomas books, I felt as if he had plagarized himself...I didn't really get into the main character, found the situation to be too unrealistic to be relatable. But don't take my word for it, the Odd Thomas series has never been my favorites, I read them once and then never again. I am a great fan of his stand alone books, of which there are over 60. I collect them and I am currently doing a Koontz re-read of all his titles that have come out since I was a teenager. I've read every one, and am not going through them again, this time faster, seeing how I take them...Will they be the same story? What will I notice that wasn't there before? Will I even like it? <br />Unfortunately, this has never been one of my favorites.<br />I am such a Koontz fan, I really hate writing a bad review, a part of me is actually afraid he will read it and then all my years and millions of pages of fan-hood will have been in vain, and I will be the most hated thing in the world- misunderstood. <br />SO, I am saying this, with love....not my favorite. Sorry!</span>
  <a data-text-id="3747618917259174555" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


